</div>



    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Central California Coast</b> (261Ac, Aj-l). Stands vary in plant height, cover, and species composition at Cone Peak Gradient RNA (Cheng 2004).</li>
        
            <li><b>Central California Coast Ranges</b> (M262Aa-f, Ah, Aj). Stands on Coyote Ridge (Evens and San 2004) and the San Benito Mountain (Evens et al. 2006) areas in the Diablo Range, from the Santa Lucia Mountains (Borchert et al. 2004), from Pinnacles National Monument (Kittel et al. 2012), and as far north as Mount Diablo and at Briones Regional Park in Contra Costa Co. occur adjacent to stands of the <i>Adenostoma fasciculatum</i> alliance on fine-grained sediments.</li>
        
            <li><b>Southern California Coast</b> (261Ba-j). Stands sampled in central San Diego Co. (Evens and San 2005), Santa Monica Mountains, (Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006), and generally in the section (Borchert et al. 2004) are extensive. On the Channel Islands, <i>Salvia mellifera </i>forms stands on Santa Catalina (Dixon et al. 2019) and Santa Cruz (Rodriguez et al. 2017).</li>
        
            <li><b>Southern California Mountains and Valleys</b> (M262Ba-d, Bf, Bj-l, Bn). Stands in this section best characterize the alliance (Kirkpatrick and Hutchinson 1977, Malanson 1984, Mooney 1977, White and Padley 1997, Borchert et al. 2004).</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Salvia mellifera </i>stands are declining in wildland settings. Invasions of non-native annual grasses have increased fire frequency and reduced seed banks. Fire, these grasses, <i>Brassica nigra</i>, and air pollution reduce the success of <i>S. mellifera</i>. Successful restoration must create conditions in which shrubs can establish, mature, and develop seed banks (Montalvo and McMillan 2002b). </div>
</div>

    

    

